{{Infobox |name = International Sufi Festival India |bodystyle = |titlestyle = |abovestyle = background:#E9967A; |subheaderstyle = |title = |above = International Sufi Festival India |image = |caption = |headerstyle = background:#EDC9AF; |header1 = General Information |label2 = Related genres |data2 = |label3 = Location |data3 = [[Ajmer]] and [[Noida Film City]] |label4 = Related events |data4 = [[Sufism]], [[Mysticism]], [[Convention (meeting)|Conference]], [[Sufi music]], [[Exhibition]] |label5 = Organizer |data5 = Gulsha Begum |label6 = Associate Organizations |data6 = Divine abode, Kamaluddin Charitable Trust and Marwah Studios }}
'''International Sufi Festival India''' is an annual program to promote the teaching of [[Sufism]] and disseminate its knowledge.<ref name="Fest 1">{{cite news|title=International Sufi Film Festival 2012 At Ajmer|url=http://asms.edu.in/news-events.html|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref><ref name="Fest 4"/><ref name="Fest 6"/>
==Venue== Since its 4th session in 2014, it is taking place at [[Ajmer]] and [[Noida Film City]] in [[Delhi]] after accomplishment of three-major International [[Sufi]] Festival in [[Ajmer]].<ref name="Fest 6"/><ref name="Fest 5">{{cite web|title=4th International Sufi Festival India 2014 at Marwah Studios|url=http://gffn.org/4th-international-sufi-festival-india-2014-at-marwah-studios/|website=International Film & Television Club|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref><ref name="Fest 7">{{cite news|title=Ajmer set to host first global Sufi fest|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/art-and-theatre/ajmer-set-to-host-first-global-sufi-fest_96896.html|accessdate=17 December 2015|publisher=Zeenews.com|date=23 September 2011}}</ref>
==Aim== The festival basically aimed to focus on spirituality by spreading the thought and message of Peace and Humanity of the Sufi saint [[Moinuddin Chishti|Khwaja Moinuddin Chishty]].<ref name="Fest 4"/><ref name="Fest 5"/><ref name="Fest 2">{{cite news|title=Sufi film festival in Ajmer from October 4|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/Sufi-film-festival-in-Ajmer-from-October-4/articleshow/16402852.cms|accessdate=16 December 2015|publisher=The Times of India}}</ref>
==Features== It is featured by conference, Sufi Musical segment (Mehfils) and Sufi films along with the exhibition of [[Persian language|Persian]] calligraphy, art, Arabic Islamic antique prints, Rumi paintings, abstract sacred art, Sufi text, literature and Poetry.<ref name="Fest 4"/><ref name="Fest 7"/><ref name="Fest 2"/><ref name="Fest 3">{{cite web|title=International Sufi Film Festival 2012 At Ajmer|url=http://asms.edu.in/news-events.html|website=Asian School of Media Studies|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>
==Organizer== Gulsha Begum the festival director & Chairperson of Kamaluddin Charitable Trust is the inducer. She organize the festival in association with Divine abode, Kamaluddin Charitable Trust and Marwah Studios.<ref name="Fest 1"/><ref name="Fest 5"/><ref name="Fest 2"/><ref name="Fest 3"/>
==International contributors== Participants and performers from India, Egypt, Germany, Pakistan, U.K., Russia and some other countries take part in the festival.<ref name="Fest 4">{{cite web|title=International Sufi Film Festival 2012 At Ajmer|url=http://aspa.edu.in/news.html|website=ASPA - Asian School of Performing Arts|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref><ref name="Fest 7"/>
==Schedule== The 5th International Sufi Festival India will take place on 17 December 2015.<ref name="Fest 6">{{cite web|title=5th International Sufi Festival in Noida|url=http://www.free-press-release.com/news-5th-international-sufi-festival-in-noida-1449834529.html|website=Pre Press Release|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>
