[[File:Roma-sanpietroin vincoli01.jpg|300px|thumb|right|The first papal election following ''[[In Nomine Domini]]'' (1059) took place in [[San Pietro in Vincoli]] ("Saint Peter in Chains") rather than [[Old St. Peter's Basilica]] due to intense secular opposition to the new papal selection process.]]
There have been 110 papal elections that have produced [[List of popes|popes currently recognized]] by the [[Catholic Church]] as legitimate. There was no fixed process for [[papal selection before 1059|papal succession before 1059]] and [[pope]]s were often selected with substantial secular involvement, if not [[papal appointment|outright appointment]]. Since the promulgation of ''[[In nomine Domini]]'' (1059), however, suffrage has been limited to the [[College of Cardinals]].<ref>Johannes Baptist Sägmüller, "[[s:Catholic Encyclopedia (1913)/Cardinal (1)|Cardinal]]" in ''[[Catholic Encyclopedia]]'' (1913).</ref>

Papal elections since 1276 have taken the form of [[papal conclave]]s, which are elections that follow a set of rules and procedures developed in ''[[Ubi periculum]]'' (1274) and later [[papal bull]]s; observance of the conclave varied until 1294, but all papal elections since have followed relatively similar conclave procedures.

Although the [[cardinal (Catholicism)|cardinals]] have historically gathered at a handful of other locations within Rome and beyond, only five elections since 1455 have been held outside the [[Apostolic Palace]].<ref name="baumsix"/> Twenty-eight papal elections have been held outside Rome, in: [[Terracina]] (1088), [[Cluny]] (1119), [[Velletri]] (1181), [[Verona]] (1185), [[Ferrara]] (October 1187), [[Pisa]] (December 1187), [[Perugia Papacy|Perugia]] (1216, 1264&ndash;1265, 1285, 1292&ndash;1294, 1304&ndash;1305), [[Anagni]] (1243), [[Naples]] (1254, 1294), [[Viterbo Papacy|Viterbo]] (1261, 1268&ndash;1271, July 1276, August–September 1276, 1277, 1281&ndash;1282), [[Arezzo]] (January 1276), [[Carpentras]]/[[Lyon]] (1314&ndash;1316), [[Avignon Papacy|Avignon]] (1334, 1342, 1352, 1362, 1370), [[Konstanz]] (1417) and [[Venice]] (1799&ndash;1800). Three elections moved between locations while in progress: the elections of [[Papal election, 1268–71|1268–71]], [[Papal election, 1292–94|1292–94]], and [[Papal conclave, 1314–16|1314–16]].

