{{Infobox Convention | name = Shinboku-con | image = | caption = | status = Defunct | genre = [[Anime]], [[Role-playing game|Role-playing]]<ref name="AC-2013"/> | venue = Sawmill Creek Resort | location = [[Huron, Ohio]] | country = United States | first = 2007 | last = 2014 | organizer = LCCC Anime Society & Roleplayer's Association<ref name="sc2007"/> | attendance = 743 in 2013 | website = }}
'''Shinboku-con''' was an annual four-day anime convention held during April at the Sawmill Creek Resort in [[Huron, Ohio]].
==Programming== The convention typically offers anime showings, cosplay contest, dances, panels, professional wrestling, trading card tournaments, vendors/artist room, and video game tournaments.<ref name="AC-2013"/>
==History== Shinboku-con was founded in 2007 by members of the [[Lorain County Community College]] Anime Society and Roleplayer's Association.<ref name="sc2007">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/press/post/470/lorain-county-community-college-to-host-anime-con | title = Lorain County Community College to host anime con | publisher = AnimeCons.com | date = 2007-04-03 | accessdate = 2018-06-06}}</ref> In 2010 the convention became a three-day event, and had its first industry guest, [[Tiffany Grant]].<ref name="ac10shin">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/press/post/1048/tiffany-grant-and-gavin-goszka-to-appear-at-shinboku-con-2010 | title = Tiffany Grant and Gavin Goszka to appear at Shinboku-con 2010 | publisher = AnimeCons.com | date = 2010-02-17 | accessdate = 2018-06-06}}</ref> In 2011 three attendees were arrested at the convention, two men were involved in a dispute over the playing of a video game which resulted in a punch to the mouth and an officer being spit on. Another man was arrested for an incident involving the damage of hotel property and underage consumption of alcohol.<ref name="kotaku11">{{cite web|title=Kotaku: Three Men Arrested after Fisticuffs at Nerd Convention|url=http://kotaku.com/shinboku_con-2011/|accessdate=2012-03-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://westlake.patch.com/articles/police-blotter-man-spits-on-officer-at-video-game-convention | title = Police Blotter: Man Spits on Officer at Video Game Convention | publisher = WestlakePatch | accessdate = 2012-05-06}}</ref> The convention expanded to a partial fourth day in 2014.<ref name="AC-2014"/> Shinboku-con cancelled their 2015 event.<ref name="AC-2015">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/6025/shinboku-con-2015 | title = Shinboku Con 2015 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2018-06-06}}</ref>
